article.headline: Tulane 73, Rice 67
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Ben Benfield had 18 points, seven rebounds and three assists as Tulane rallied to defeat Rice 73-67 on Saturday. Tulane (4-1) trailed for much of the game, but took a 54-52 lead on a fast-break lay-in by Marcus Kinzer. Kinzer had 11 points and six assists for the game. Rice (4-2) tied the game at 54 on a jumper by J.R. Harrison, but a tip-in by Vytas Tatarunas put the Green Wave on top for good. Tatarunas had 12 points and eight rebounds. The Owls hit 1-of-2 free throws but Kinzer connected on a 3-pointer to push the margin to four with 7:29 to go. A jumper by Jason McKrieth with 4:37 to go pulled the Owls within two at 64-62, but Tulane's Kinzer and Tatarunas converted back-to-back hoops on offensive rebounds. McKrieth led Rice with 22 points, seven rebounds and seven assists. Despite struggling from the line, the Green Wave scored four points on free throws in the final 1:21 to hold on to the victory. Tulane hit 7-of-19 free throw attempts. In the first half, Rice pulled away with a 10-0 run midway through, but Tulane rallied to trail 38-32 at the break. Wayne Tinsley had 17 points, eight assists and five rebounds for the Green Wave.
